info.senderName: NWS Duluth (Northeast Minnesota and Northern Wisconsin)
info.headline: Flood Advisory issued September 24 at 12:22AM CDT by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 115 AM CDT EARLY THIS MORNING... * WHAT...Urban and small stream flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected. * WHERE...In Minnesota, Lake and St. Louis Counties. * WHEN...Until 115 AM CDT Sunday. * IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas. Ponding of water in urban or other areas is occurring or is imminent, including the city of Two Harbors. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 1219 AM CDT Sunday, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to thunderstorms. This will cause urban and small stream flooding. Between 1 and 2 inches of rain have fallen. - Additional rainfall amounts of 1 to 2 inches are expected over the area. This additional rain will result in minor flooding. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... Two Harbors, Knife River, Stoney Point, Larsmont, French River and Palmers. - Flood safety information can be found at www.weather.gov/safety/flood.
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Be especially cautious at night when it is harder to recognize the dangers of flooding.
